# Backend Rules

- PostgreSQL is the source of truth for persistent domain data.
- Dream text is immutable; store annotations, summaries and analysis separately.
- Backend services own session lifecycle and business logic.
- Routers define HTTP contracts and dependency wiring, not domain behavior.
- Bot, Mini App and AI providers must not access the database directly.
- Every analytical flow should be session-aware unless explicitly designed otherwise.
- Prefer isolated services with deterministic behavior and focused tests.
- Schema changes must go through Alembic migrations.
